<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When I create a form using array notation, some elements should not follow the rule from the main form.
For example:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form = new Zend_Form;
$form-&gt;setElementsBelongTo('Foo');
$form-&gt;addElement('text', 'name');
$form-&gt;addElement('text', 'email');
$form-&gt;addElement('text', 'Bar', array('belongsTo' =&gt; 'subInfo'));
</code></pre>

<p>The output is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
</code></pre>

<p>While the correct output (because setBelongsTo() was called individualy) is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
</code></pre>

